 September 12 at Swabhumi; 6 pm: Bengali modern songs by Debosrita Basu. 

 September 13 at Rabindra Sadan; 5.45 pm: Chakratirtha?s first anniversary programme features Desh Dekhachchho Andhakare? ? recitation by Pradip Ghosh, Kajal Sur, Kingshuk Roy Choudhury, Shuktisree Saha, Anutosh Mukherjee, Basabdatta Majumdar, Dalia Basu Saha, Tuhina Dutta, Subir Dhar, Anupam Choudhury, Pritha Mukherjee Ghosh, Kakali Chakraborty, Samir Ghosh, Indrani Ghosh and Chhanda Chatterjee; songs by Suman Panthi, Debasree Biswas, Apala Basu and Sumita Pal; dance by Meghamala Aich Roy, Angana Joardar, Satabdi Rakshit and Suchhanda Sarkar. Concept amp; direction: Kajal Sur. 

 September 13 at Bharatiyam, IB 201 Salt Lake; 6 pm: EZCC presents a Kathak dance recital by Sudeshna Maulik and her troupe. 

 September 14 at Madhusudan Mancha; 6 pm: Lake Gardens Anandam presents recitation by Bratati Bandyopadhyay and the play, Mrs. Soriano, produced by Choopkatha. 

 September 15 at Jibanananda Sabhaghar; 5.30 pm: Souhardya 70 hosts its monthly poetry-reading session along with discussion and painting. Participants include Utpal Kumar Basu (discussion), Nabaneeta Dev Sen, Sudhendu Mallick, Ardhendu Chakraborty, Namita Choudhury, Amitabha Chowdhury, Sandip Chattopadhyay, Sangita Bandyopadhyay and Susmeli Dutta in poetry-reading; Abhik Basu (nursery rhymes), Hiranmoy Mitra (painting) and Moushumi Karmakar (songs). 

 September 15 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Vivekananda Hall; 6 pm: A sarod recital by Suro Ranjan Mukherjee with Arup Chattopadhyay on the tabla. 

 September 15 at Gyan Manch; 6.30 pm: Padatik Dance Centre presents an evening of Kathak dance by its students. Choreography: Madhumita Roy, Souvik Chakraborty, Bidisha Banerjee, Mitul Sengupta and Sandip Mullick. 

 talk

