 Till September 26 at P-249 Purna Das Road; 11 am: Darbari?s lifestyle section offers products from NGOs and artisans who have not been able to secure a direct retail outlet for their products, which include cushion covers, mobile and patchwork bags, short tops, Madhubani paintings, dokra, glazed terracotta pottery, stationery, wood and metal furniture. 

 DISCOURSE

 Till September 14 at Jyotirmai Club, 37/1A Garcha Road; 3.30 pm - 7 pm: Shrimad Bhagwat Gyan Yagna. Discourse by Ma Purnananda. 

 SEMINAR

 September 12, 13 amp; 15 at Nandan II; 6.30 pm: Three seminar sessions on various facets of Bengali cinema. September 12: Rituparno Ghosh will deliberate on the language of literature and the language of cinema. September 13: Debajyoti Mishra and Mousumi Bhowmick will speak on Role of Music in Bengali Cinema. September 15: Goutam Ghose will speak on Experiment of Form in Bengali Cinema.Organised by Cine Central Calcutta, BFJA and Anamika Kala Sangam along with Srilab Communication Pvt. Ltd. 

 WORKSHOP

 September 15 - 18 at 12B Russel Street, 8th floor (opp. Canara Bank); 10 am - 12 noon: The Art of Living workshop for media professionals. Last date of registration: September 13 by 2 pm. For queries, kolkataartofliving.org 

